  "texts": [
    "While the intention to eat healthier exists, it rarely translates into behavior, particularly without supporting structures like transparent nutrition displays or healthier defaults.",
    "Supporting this, cross-tabulation results (Table 14) show that nutritional awareness exists even among frequent users.",
    "Over 64% of those ordering more than five times weekly agreed or strongly agreed that they considered nutrition, with the highest rate of \"strongly agree\" (26.47%) across all groups.",
    "It suggests that frequent diners can become more reflective with time, possibly due to increased exposure to menus and food-for-thought stockpiling.",
    "This finding challenges the assumption that a high ordering frequency is evidence of nutrition omission."
  ],
